'''''Kroonika''''' (meaning ''The Chronicle'' in English)<ref name=kir>{{cite web|title=Kroonika|url=http://kirjastus.ee/admin/upload/images/Kroonika_ENG.pdf|publisher=Kirjastus|accessdate=4 September 2014}}</ref> is a popular [[Estonia]]n [[magazine]] which is typically popular with young Estonian persons aged between 13 and 30 years of age. 

==History and profile==
''Kroonika'' was established in 1996.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Barbi Pilvre|title=Estonian men’s lifestyle magazine ‘Mees’: a manual of masculine identity in a transition society|journal=ETIS|url=https://www.etis.ee/File/DownloadPublic/49c2027c-cc4f-439b-b714-863e081460dd?name=Fail_Est.men%C2%B4s%20lifestyle%20manual.pdf&type=application%2Fpdf|accessdate=22 April 2017}}</ref> Its publisher is AS Ajakirjade Kirjastus.<ref>{{cite web|title=AS Ajakirjade Kirjastus|url=http://www.egrupp.ee/companies/as-ajakirjade-kirjastus|work=Ekspress Grupp|accessdate=4 September 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140904150059/http://www.egrupp.ee/companies/as-ajakirjade-kirjastus|archivedate=4 September 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The magazine is published in the [[Estonian language]], and includes gossip and news on the country's biggest [[celebrity|celebrities]]. It is published weekly on Fridays and is based in [[Tallinn]].<ref name=kir/> Its [[editor-in-chief]] is Krista Lensin.<ref name=kir/>

