{{Use British English|date=September 2018}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}
'''Operation Yellowhammer''' is the codename for "no-deal" contingency planning by the [[United Kingdom|UK]] [[HM Treasury|Treasury]] in the event [[Brexit negotiations]] for the [[Withdrawal from the European Union|withdrawal]] from the European Union fail to reach an agreement or an extension by 29 March 2019.<ref name="Ind20180906">{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/operation-yellowhammer-brexit-photo-eu-rail-access-nodeal-secret-paper-latest-document-a8525506.html |title=Operation Yellowhammer: Photo of secret government no-deal Brexit papers reveals questions over 'rail access to the EU |date=6 September 2018 |newspaper=The Independent|url-access=limited}}</ref>

Should there fail to be a negotiated settlement by 29 March 2019 then the UK would leave the [[European Union]], leaving a hiatus impacting many aspects of the relationship between the UK and European Union.  The areas impacted would include money, citizens, trade, customs, and regulations.<ref name="BBC-nodeal-look">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-39294904|title=Brexit: What would 'no deal' look like?|first=Chris|last=Morris|date=14 October 2017|access-date=6 September 2018|website=BBC}}</ref>

On 6 September 2018 a press photographer captured a snapshot of a "no-deal" planning document revealing some details of then-current preparations and the [[HM Treasury]] codename for those plans.<ref name="BBCsnatchPIC">{{cite news|title=Snatched pic gives insight into 'no deal' Brexit planning|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-45410344|first=Laura|last=Kuenssberg|date=6 September 2018|access-date=6 September 2018}}</ref> The document appeared to indicate the [[Civil Contingencies Secretariat]], a department of the [[Cabinet Office]] responsible for emergency planning, had been used in anticipation of government policy.<ref name="Sky-FI1">{{cite news|url=https://news.sky.com/story/operation-yellowhammer-leaked-no-deal-brexit-details-are-quite-revealing-11491983|title=It's been another first for Brexit.|access-date=7 September 2018|first=Faisal|last=Islam|website=Sky}}</ref> No further details were revealed.

