{{context|date=May 2018}} {| class="toccolours" style="float: right; margin: 0 0 1em 1em;" |colspan="2" style="background: #efefef; text-align: center;"| '''WTO Ministerial Conference of 2017''' |- |colspan="2" style="text-align: center;"| |- style="vertical-align:top;" | '''Opening ceremony''' | 11 December 2017 |- style="vertical-align:top;" | '''Closing ceremony''' | 13 December 2017 |- style="vertical-align:top;" | '''Conference venue''' | [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] |- style="vertical-align:top;" | Website | [https://www.wto.org/english/thewto_e/minist_e/mc11_e/mc11_e.htm] |} {{Location map |Earth |label = |label_size = |position = |background = |lat = -34.6334 |long = -58.3667 |marksize = 5 |border = |caption = Location of Buenos Aires |float = right |width = 320 }}
The 11th [[World Trade Organization]] [[Ministerial Conference]] was held in Buenos Aires, Argentina, from 11 to 13 December 2017. It was chaired by Minister Susana Malcorra of Argentina. The Conference ended with a number of ministerial decisions, including on fisheries subsidies and e-commerce duties, and a commitment to continue negotiations in all areas. The conference also led to the formation of working party to enable faster induction of South Sudan in the WTO.<ref>https://www.wto.org/english/thewto_e/minist_e/mc11_e/mc11_e.htm</ref>
